      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Before starting the commissioning process the following must
be checked:</p>
         <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Make sure that you are familiar
with the actual system, have studied the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Single Line Diagram</i> and know the position of all the switches, breakers and feeders.</note>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check with a properly rated measuring device that all sections
are de-energized.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all protective earth connections and interconnections
(between transport units) are secured and undamaged.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all connectors are firmly fixed.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all printed circuit boards (PCBs) are correctly
mounted and that all plugs are firmly plugged in.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all interconnections and junctions are according
to specifications, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Connection Diagram</i>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all external fuses have the correct size, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Technical Data</i>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Remove all bags with moisture absorbing material left in the
cabinets.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the interior of the system is completely dry.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that all switches and breakers have the correct status
according to the following table.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
